question.title: Maven clean install fails due to missing dependency from Bintray/JFrog (jade-plugin-common)
question.body:
I'm working on a legacy Java 8 project. When I run the command mvn clean install, the build fails due to a dependency resolution issue. Hereâ€™s the relevant part of the error:

[ERROR] Failed to execute goal on project impl: Could not resolve dependencies for project com.unionsystems.trade:impl:war:1.0-SNAPSHOT: 
Failed to collect dependencies at net.sf.cssbox:pdf2dom:jar:1.6 
-> net.mabboud.fontverter:FontVerter:jar:1.2.18 
-> org.reflections:reflections-maven:jar:0.9.9-RC2 
-> org.jfrog.jade.plugins.common:jade-plugin-common:jar:1.3.8: 
Failed to read artifact descriptor for org.jfrog.jade.plugins.common:jade-plugin-common:jar:1.3.8: 
Could not transfer artifact org.jfrog.jade.plugins.common:jade-plugin-common:pom:1.3.8 
from/to maven-default-http-blocker (http://0.0.0.0/): 
Blocked mirror for repositories: [bintray-nitram509-jbrotli (http://dl.bintray.com/nitram509/jbrotli, default, releases+snapshots), 
jfrog-plugins (http://repo.jfrog.org/artifactory/plugins-releases, default, releases+snapshots)]

It seems the build is trying to fetch a dependency from an old JFrog/Bintray repository that is no longer available (or blocked by Maven due to HTTP).

What I've Tried:

  • Running with -e and -X flags for more logging.
  • Searching for an alternative repository or mirror for the missing jade-plugin-common:1.3.8.
  • Checking if there's a way to bypass or manually install the dependency.

My Questions:

  1. How can I resolve this dependency issue?

Any help or direction would be appreciated. Thank you!

question_comments.body: If you google the jars, you can still download them. I'm not going to link, download at your own risk. If you do not have a nexus of your own setup to which you can upload third party jars, you have the option of creating a maven repository inside your project and host the jars as part of the code base. For now, because it is drastically needed that these dependencies get replaced. This answer shows how to do that: stackoverflow.com/a/28762617/424903 . If that is acceptable, I guess we can close this question as a duplicate.

You can have a look here mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.jfrog.jade.plugins.common/…, but I may just be the case that the dependency is gone. Then it might not be possible to compile the project anymore without rewriting the project.
Whoever wants to close this question because of "Seeking recommendations for software libraries, tutorials, tools, books, or other off-site resources" should read the question again, please.
